{"lemma":"ظُنْبُوبَيْ","slug":"ظُنْبُوبَيْ","root":"ظ.ن.ب","root_slug":"ظ-ن-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ظ-ن-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27710"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B8%D9%8F%D9%86%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%8F%D9%88%D8%A8%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27710","headword_ar":"ظُنْبُوبٌ","root":"Znb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"edge of the shin:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tough edge of the shin:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"external part of the shank:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shin-bone:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"edge of the shin-bone:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tough bone in the fore part of the shank:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) but accord. to AZ, this term is not used in relation to animals that have"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awoZifap","text_ar":"اَوْظِفَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": [see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waZiyfN","text_ar":"وَظِيفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] (T, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZanaAbiybu","text_ar":"ظَنَابِيبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, M, K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAriY AlZ~anaAbiybi","text_ar":"عَارِى الظَّنَابِيبِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Without flesh upon the shins"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) is an epithet applied to a male ostrich. (S, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraEa Zunobuwba AlbaEiyri","text_ar":"قَرَعَ ظُنْبُوبَ البَعِيرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He knocked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"struck, the shin of the camel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"that he might lie down, and he might mount him: or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaroEu AlZ~unobuwbi","text_ar":"قَرْعُ الظُّنْبُوبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies a man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knocking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"striking, the shin"},{"kind":"text","text":"of his camel with his stick when he makes him lie down that he may mount him, as one in haste to betake himself to a thing: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"striking the shin"},{"kind":"text","text":"of his beast with his whip, [in the TA is here added"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lytrqh","text_ar":"ليترقه"},{"kind":"text","text":", which I can only suppose to be put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liyuborikahu","text_ar":"لِيُبْرِكَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", to make him lie down,] when he desires to mount him. (TA.) [See an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuroquwbN","text_ar":"عُرْقُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraEa","text_ar":"قَرَعَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN liA^amorihi Zunobuwbahu","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ لِاَمْرِهِ ظُنْبُوبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one struck his shin to betake himself to his affair"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a one applied himself to his affair with diligence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"energy."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, L, TA.) Selámeh Ibn-Jendel says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"kun~aA A_i*aA maA A^ataAnaA SaArixN faziEN\n                      \n                     \n                        kaAna AlS~uraAxu lahu qaroEa AlZ~anaAbiybi"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We were"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such that"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when there came to us one crying aloud, in terror, the clamour"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"returned"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to him was the striking of the shins;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] by which he is said to mean that a quick reply was given; calling the striking of the whip upon the leg of the boot, in urging on the horse, “ the striking of the shin. ” (S.) You also say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraEa li*`lika AlA^amori","text_ar":"قَرَعَ لِذٰلِكَ الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zunobuwbahu","text_ar":"ظُنْبُوبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He prepared himself for that affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and agreeably with this signification the verse of Selámeh cited above has been explained. (M, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraEa ZanaAbiyba AlA^amori","text_ar":"قَرَعَ ظَنَابِيبَ الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rendered, the affair manageable."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA.) A poet, cited by IAar, says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"qaraEotu ZanaAbiyba AlohawaY yawoma EaAlijK"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I subdued love,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"subjected it to my will, on the day of 'Álij;."},{"kind":"text","text":"as though I struck it on the shins; as a camel's shin is struck when one desires him to lie down, that he may mount him. (M, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZunobuwbN","text_ar":"ظُنْبُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A nail that is in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jub~ap","text_ar":"جُبَّة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a spear-head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the part into which the shaft enters,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"where it is fixed upon the upper extremity of the shaft:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZanaAbiyb","text_ar":"ظَنَابِيب"},{"kind":"text","text":"has been said to be the pl. of the word in this sense in the verse of Selámeh cited above. (M, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","M","TA","S","T"]}]}}